🔵 PART A — Creating Bucket & Uploading Data
✅ Step 1: Create Bucket
Go to:
AWS Console → S3 → Create bucket
Enter:
Bucket name: 23BD1A052D_S3 (must be globally unique)
Region: Choose required region
❌ Uncheck Block all public access
✔ Acknowledge warning
Enable Bucket Versioning
Enable Object Ownership
Click Create bucket
✅ Step 2: Upload Objec
Open bucket
Click Upload
Select file (image, pdf, text file etc.)
Click Upload
✅ Step 3: Make Object Public
Go to Permissions
Edit ACL
Under Everyone (public access) → ✔ Read
Save
select bucket -> actions -> make public using ACL
Copy Object URL
Open in Incognito mode
✔ File loads publicly

🔵 PART B — Versioning & Delete Marker
🔹 Delete Object
Select file
Click Delete
It disappears from normal view.
🔹 Show Versions
Enable Show versions
You will see:
Delete marker
Previous object version
🔹 Remove Delete Marker
Select delete marker
Click Delete
✔ Original object is restored

🔵 PART C — Cross Region Replication (CRR)
⚠ Prerequisites
✔ Versioning enabled on both buckets
✔ Buckets in different regions
✅ Step 1: Create Destination Bucket
Create new bucket in another region
Enable versioning.
✅ Step 2: Create Replication Rule
Open Source bucket
Go to Management
Click Create replication rule
Fill:
Rule name
Apply to all objects
Destination bucket (other region)
Select LabRole / AWS-managed role
Click Save.
✅ Step 3: Test Replication
Upload new file to source bucket.
Now check destination bucket

🔵 PART D — Static Website Hosting
✅ Step 1: Upload Files
Upload:
index.html
error.html
✅ Step 2: Enable Static Hosting
Go to Properties
Scroll to Static Website Hosting
Click Edit
Enable
Enter:
Index: index.html
Error: error.html
Save
✅ Step 3: Make Public
Enable public read at:
Bucket level (ACL)
Object level (ACL)
✅ Step 4: Access Website
Copy:
Bucket Website Endpoint which is in permissions scroll down (swh)
Example:
http://bucket-name.s3-website-region.amazonaws.com
Open in browser.
✔ Website loads
